summary: Amazing Spider-Man #245 (October 1983) The mystery of the person beneath the Hobgoblin mask was probably the most exciting era...
caption:
Amazing Spider-Man #245 (October 1983)

The mystery of the person beneath the Hobgoblin mask was probably the most exciting era to be reading Amazing Spider-Man in my lifetime. For my money, it is second only to the original Green Goblin saga as an ongoing story. 

It was this ongoing storyline that really got me into reading the letters columns of comics, since ASM’s letters at the time gave over a lot of space to people giving their guesses and reasoning for who was behind the mask.

Of course, the eventual reveal that the Hobogoblin was Ned Leeds was unsatisfying… and the dude in this issue was not really the Hobgoblin either. Many years later it’d turn out it wasn’t Ned Leeds either.

summary: His Hater (Peter Parker x Reader) Summary: Internet is breaking with both innocent and non-innocent thoughts of Spider-man....
body:
His Hater (Peter Parker x Reader)

Summary: Internet is breaking with both innocent and non-innocent thoughts of Spider-man. Someone is having none of it.

A/N: I only wrote this out of boredom and was actually surprised that this little piece of work had gotten supports. Also please ignore the date and time. I just finished my homeworks when I started to write this. Anyway, here you go! (Please also bear in mind that this is my first time writing a Spider-man fan fiction. I’m so sorry in advance if he’s OOC. Chapters are also going to be short. You can correct me on the comment, or you can dm me. :) )

Chapter 1: “Dear Mr. Spider-man,”

Peter smugly smiled as he walked pass his chatting school mates. He felt his chest swell with pride as his secret persona becomes the topic of not only his school, but also the internet.

“Spider-man is so awesome!”

“I know right? I wonder how long he trained those backflips.”

“Trained? I bet you my liver it’s natural for him!”

“What? You think he got bitten by a rare spider, giving him those superhuman abilities, or something?”

“What? It’s a possibility!”

He smirked, slightly shaking his head. His theory sounds dumb, but who was Peter kidding? The idea of Spider-man himself was dumber.

It’s not long after his best pal, Ned, came up running to him.

“Hey, spider,” Ned took notice of his friend’s broad smile. “you seemed extra happy today. Got somethin’ you wanna share?”

“Nothing. It’s just…” Peter sheepishly looked at him. Ned’s mouth formed an “o” shaped in realization.

Ned quickly pulled out his phone, and unlocked it to shove it to Peter’s face, “Speaking of which, look at these!”

“Oh.”

summary: With the news of Spider-Man One More Day being reversed showing up....
title: With the news of Spider-Man One More Day being reversed showing up....
body:
I do hope this won’t mean that the good stuff we did get out of the post One More Day years like Silk for example will vanish from existence and never happened because that would be honestly throwing the baby out with the bath water. I know this is great news for Spider Man fans and I imagine Linkara especially is happy to hear about that but I don’t want to see a character like Cindy Moon AKA Silk that I’ve grown to like a lot gotten rid of as a result.

I could be overreacting a little and this could be in the end like DC’s Rebirth where while it’s a return to form of the original set up a lot of the new stuff/characters still happened and if that’s the case here that’s awesome. :)
